Buckeye.Waterman Wash: Waterman Wash is a tributary steam or arroyo of the Gila River, in Maricopa County, Arizona. Its mouth is at its confluence with the Gila River in the Buckeye Valley at an elevation of 843 feet / 257 meters. Is source is at 33°07′11″N 112°13′10″W at an elevation of 2,400 feet on Sevenmile Mountain.
